CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1784135919
OL,3,CHosepipe ban comes into force in parts
OL,4,Cof Devon
OL,6,FPeople are advised not to use
OL,7,Fhosepipes for watering gardens,
OL,8,Fwashing cars, patios and boats, or
OL,9,Ffilling swimming and paddling pools.
OL,11,FTwo extreme heatwaves in the last few
OL,12,Fweeks have driven up "high demand" in
OL,13,Fthe region by around 5.4 million
OL,14,Flitres per day.
OL,16,FThe firm says this has placed huge
OL,17,Fpressure on the local drinking water
OL,18,Fsupply network.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1784135919
OL,3,CHosepipe ban comes into force in parts
OL,4,Cof Devon
OL,6,FThe hosepipe restrictions covers
OL,7,Fanything that connects to the mains
OL,8,Fsupply. The ban applies to sprinklers,
OL,9,Firrigations systems and pressure
OL,10,Fwashers as well as to hosepipes.
OL,12,FAccording to the Met Office,
OL,13,Ftemperatures have reached 35C or
OL,14,Fhigher in May, June and July of the
OL,15,Fsame year, marking the first time this
OL,16,Fhas happened in the UK weather record.
OL,18,FThe South West has been placed under a
OL,19,Fyellow heat health warning by the UK
OL,20,FHealth Security Agency (UKHSA) until
OL,21,FFriday (17 July) at 9pm.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1784135919
OL,3,CHosepipe ban comes into force in parts
OL,4,Cof Devon
OL,6,FIt means significant impacts are
OL,7,F"possible" across health and social
OL,8,Fcare services due to the high
OL,9,Ftemperatures, including a rise in
OL,10,Fdeaths, particularly among those aged
OL,11,F65 and over, or with health conditions.
OL,13,FHosepipe ban exemptions
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1784135919
OL,3,CHosepipe ban comes into force in parts
OL,4,Cof Devon
OL,6,FPeople who need to use a hosepipe
OL,7,Fbecause of medical needs, a disability
OL,8,For other personal circumstances may be
OL,9,Fexempt from the restrictions,
OL,10,Fincluding those with a Blue Badge,
OL,11,Fthose registered on South West Water's
OL,12,FPriority Services Register, or who
OL,13,Freceive support through a WaterSure
OL,14,Ftariff.
OL,16,FThose who also need a hosepipe to
OL,17,Fprotect human health and safety, or
OL,18,Ffor animal welfare, may be exempt.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
